Such VDFs can be described as κ-functions or generalised Lorentzians, and are a key property of the modern exospheric model VDFs that are assumed to exist at the exobase, which was assumed to be located at r0 = 2 R⊙ in the recent models, e.g., Pierrard and Lemaire (1996). The non-thermal K-VDF (see the paper of Maksimovic et al., 1997a) reads as a function of the particle speed υ as follows: 6\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
