A less ambitious approach was taken by (Vocks and Marsch, 2002) who have shown that it may be meaningful to simplify the full problem and reduce the kinetic VDF further by an integration over υ⊥. This procedure, used before by Dum et al. (1980) to solve dispersion relations, yields two reduced VDFs which are defined as follows: 65\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
